# Walkthrough - Fix Fall Recovery Rope Detection

## Problem
When the character fell, the system reported "找不到可用的繩索點" (Cannot find available rope point) even though there was a valid rope nearby.
This happened because the [OnFallDetected](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/UI/MainForm.cs#2676-2717) logic was restricted to searching only for explicit [ClimbUp](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs#1189-1213) waypoints in the recorded path. It ignored the [RopeData](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Models/PathPlanning/RopeData.cs#6-28) (implicit ropes loaded from map/config) which the user relies on.

## Solution

### 1. Update [MainForm.cs](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/UI/MainForm.cs) - [OnFallDetected](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/UI/MainForm.cs#2676-2717)
*   **Change:** Added a fallback search mechanism.
*   **Logic:**
    1.  First, try `tracker.FindNearestClimbUpNode(playerPos)` (Original logic - finds recorded waypoints).
    2.  If that returns null, try `tracker.FindNearbyClimbPoint(playerPos, targetPos.Y)` (New logic - searches [RopeData](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Models/PathPlanning/RopeData.cs#6-28) with spatial queries).
*   **Impact:** The system can now "see" and use any loaded rope for recovery, regardless of whether it was explicitly recorded as a step in the path.

## Verification
*   **Code Review:** Verified [MainForm.cs](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/UI/MainForm.cs) now invokes [FindNearbyClimbPoint](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs#1265-1322).
*   **Tolerance:** [FindNearbyClimbPoint](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs#1265-1322) already includes a `BottomY + 10` tolerance buffer, so it will correctly detect the rope even if the character is slightly below the visual bottom (fixing the root cause of the previous failure where PlayerY > RopeBottomY).
*   **Visuals:** This fix works purely on logic, requiring no changes to the visual rope length (preserving the clean WYSIWYG view).
